aunchAndTrack`):**\n- Auto-rebuilds image if project Dockerfile has changed (via `ImageEnsurer` interface)\n- Captures Git HEAD SHA at run start for result branch creation\n- Calls `container.Start()` with `ContainerConfig`\n- Records container ID in run and updates store to \"running\"\n- Delegates to `trackRun()` for lifetime management\n\n### 2. **The ContainerRuntime Interface** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` (lines 24-33)\n\n**Core methods:**\n- `Start(ctx, cfg)` → containerID: Creates and starts container with config\n- `Stop(ctx, containerID)`: Sends stop signal\n- `AttachOutput(ctx, containerID)` → io.ReadCloser: Streams agent output\n- `Wait(ctx, containerID)` → exitCode: Blocks until container exits\n- `CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, srcPath, dstPath)`: Extracts files from container\n- `Logs(ctx, containerID)` → string: Retrieves full container logs\n- `Remove(ctx, containerID)`: Deletes container\n- `Inspect(ctx, containerID)` → ContainerStatus: Returns running state, exit code, finish time\n\n**Optional interface:**\n- `ImageEnsurer` (lines 38-40): `EnsureImage(ctx, projectDir, image)` for rebuild checking\n\n### 3. **Docker Adapter Implementation** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 27-152)\n\n**Container startup (`Start` method, lines 27-152):**\n1. Builds `docker create` args with:\n   - Workdir: `/workspace`\n   - Host gateway: `host.docker.internal:host-gateway`\n   - Default command wrapping (as root, then `su agent`): `chown workspace, strip .serena, exec cloche-agent`\n   - Environment: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (if set), extra env via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n   - Volume mounts via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS`\n2. Executes `docker create` (captures container ID from stdout)\n3. Copies project files: `docker cp <projectDir>/. <container>:/workspace/`\n4. Applies overrides: `docker cp <projectDir>/.cloche/overrides/. <container>:/workspace/` (non-fatal if missing)\n5. Copies Claude auth: `~/.claude/` and `~/.claude.json` into container (each gets own copy)\n6. Executes `docker start` to begin container\n\nOther methods wrap `docker` CLI commands (stop, logs, wait, inspect, etc.)\n\n### 4. **Domain Types: Run, Workflow, Step** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**Run struct:**\n- `ID`, `WorkflowName`: Run identifier\n- `State`: pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled\n- `ActiveSteps`: []string (steps currently executing)\n- `StepExecutions`: []*StepExecution (logs, results, timing)\n- `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`: Timestamps\n- `ProjectDir`: Root directory of project\n- `ErrorMessage`: Failure reason\n- `ContainerID`: Docker container ID\n- `BaseSHA`: Git HEAD at run start (for result branch creation)\n- `ContainerKept`: Whether container was retained for debugging\n\n**Run lifecycle methods:**\n- `Start()`: Transition to running, record StartedAt\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName)`: Add to ActiveSteps, create StepExecution\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)`: Move from Active, mark completed\n- `Complete(state)`: Transition to success/fail, record CompletedAt\n- `Fail(msg)`: Mark failed with error message\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n\n**Workflow struct:**\n- `Name`: Identifier\n- `Steps`: map[string]*Step (step definitions)\n- `Wiring`: []Wire (result → next step routing)\n- `Collects`: []Collect (fan-in/merge logic)\n- `EntryStep`: Starting step name\n- `Config`: Workflow-level config (e.g., `container.image`)\n\n**Step struct:**\n- `Name`: Identifier\n- `Type`: agent/script/workflow\n- `Results`: []string (declared output values)\n- `Config`: map[string]string (prompt, run, timeout, max_attempts, etc.)\n\n### 5. **Image Build Tracking and Caching** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go` (lines 20-56)\n\n**`EnsureImage()` method:**\n1. Reads `.cloche/Dockerfile` from project (non-fatal if missing)\n2. Computes SHA-256 hash of Dockerfile content\n3. Queries image labels for stored `cloche.dockerfile.hash`\n4. If image doesn't exist OR hash mismatch: calls `buildImage()`\n5. Checks if base image (parsed from `FROM` directive) has changed locally:\n   - Compares stored `cloche.baseimage.digest` label to current local image ID\n   - If mismatch: rebuilds\n\n**`buildImage()` function (lines 160-188):**\n- Runs `docker build -t <image> -f <dockerfile> <projectDir>`\n- Embeds labels:\n  - `cloche.dockerfile.hash=<sha256>`: Detects Dockerfile changes\n  - `cloche.baseimage.digest=<imageID>`: Detects upstream base image updates\n- Streams build output to daemon stderr\n- Logs: `image built successfully`\n\n**Helper functions:**\n- `hashBytes()`: SHA-256 hex digest\n- `parseBaseImage()`: Extracts final `FROM` directive from Dockerfile\n- `baseImageID()`: Queries local Docker image ID via `docker inspect`\n- `imageLabel()`: Retrieves label from image\n\n### 6. **Run Lifecycle and Persistence** \n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 198-363) — `trackRun()`\n\n**Tracking loop:**\n1. Attaches to agent output via `container.AttachOutput()`, reads JSON-line status messages\n2. Fast-path log messages (no store writes)\n3. Parses protocol messages (StepStarted, StepCompleted, RunCompleted)\n4. Records step execution captures in store\n5. Closes output reader when agent finishes\n\n**Post-execution:**\n1. Waits for container exit code via `container.Wait()`\n2. Extracts output files: `docker cp <container>:/workspace/.cloche/output/. <projectDir>/.cloche/<runID>/output/`\n3. Captures full container logs to `container.log`\n4. Indexes extracted log files in log store (full.log, script logs, llm logs)\n5. Ensures run marked complete (success or fail based on exit code)\n6. Fires evolution trigger (if configured)\n7. Fires on-run-complete callback (orchestrator hook)\n8. **Extracts results to git branch** via `docker.ExtractResults()`:\n   - Uses git worktree at `.gitworktrees/cloche/<runID>`\n   - Branch name: `cloche/<runID>`\n   - Copies container workspace, commits with message: `cloche run <runID>: <workflow> (<result>)`\n   - Cleans up worktree\n9. **Container retention policy:**\n   - Failed runs: always keep (debugging)\n   - Success + `--keep-container`: keep\n   - Success without flag: remove via `container.Remove()`\n\n**Store interface (`RunStore`):**\n- `CreateRun(ctx, run)`: Insert with state=pending\n- `GetRun(ctx, id)`: Fetch by ID\n- `UpdateRun(ctx, run)`: Update all fields (state, steps, times, error, container, SHA, kept flag)\n- `ListRuns(ctx, since)`: All runs since timestamp, ordered descending\n\n**SQLite implementation:**\n- Single open connection (serialized writes, WAL mode, 5-second lock timeout)\n- Schema: `runs` table (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept)\n- Stores times as RFC3339Nano strings\n- `FailStaleRuns()` marks pending/running as failed on daemon startup (crash recovery)\n\n### 7. **Key Flow: RunWorkflow → Container → Result Branch**\n\n1. **Client calls** `RunWorkflow(workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt, keep_container)`\n2. **Daemon** creates Run in pending state, returns runID immediately\n3. **Background goroutine** (launchAndTrack):\n   - Calls `EnsureImage()` (auto-rebuild if Dockerfile changed or base image updated)\n   - Starts container with project files + overrides + Claude auth\n   - Updates run state to \"running\"\n   - Enters `trackRun()` loop\n4. **Agent inside container** executes workflow, emits JSON-line status messages to stdout\n5. **Daemon parses** status, records steps/results in store\n6. **Agent finishes** (exit code 0/non-zero)\n7. **Daemon extracts:**\n   - Output files to `.cloche/<runID>/output/`\n   - Container workspace to git branch `cloche/<runID>`\n   - Container logs\n8. **Daemon indexes** log files (full.log, script logs, LLM logs)\n9. **Container fate:** Keep (failed or flag) or remove (success without flag)\n10. **Callbacks:** Evolution trigger, orchestrator on-complete hook\n\n### Key Files\n\n- **Daemon service:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n- **Docker runtime:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`\n- **Image building:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/build.go`\n- **Result extraction:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go`\n- **Domain types:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`, `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n- **Interfaces:** `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`, `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n- **SQLite store:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n- **gRPC definitions:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- **Daemon entry:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":42198,"totalTokens":55098,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1589,"cache_read_input_tokens":50695,"output_tokens":2812,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1589},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
