[2026-03-08T01:37:29Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SdovHFFQnfxJtqjfT5cQK9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The auto-rebuild stale containers feature is already fully implemented and working. Here's a summary of how it works:\n\n**Staleness detection** (`internal/adapters/docker/build.go`):\n- `EnsureImage()` reads `.cloche/Dockerfile`, computes SHA-256 hash, and compares against a `cloche.dockerfile.hash` label stored on the image\n- If the hash differs (Dockerfile changed) or the image doesn't exist, it rebuilds\n- Additionally checks if the base image (from `FROM` directive) has changed locally by comparing `cloche.baseimage.digest` label to current image ID\n- Labels are embedded during `docker build` for future comparisons\n\n**Integration in daemon** (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go:152-162`):\n- `launchAndTrack()` calls `EnsureImage()` before starting the container\n- If the rebuild fails, the run is marked as failed with a descriptive error message\n\n**Test coverage**:\n- Unit tests for hash computation, Dockerfile parsing, no-Dockerfile case, base image staleness\n- Integration tests (Docker-dependent, skipped in this environment) for build-when-missing, skip-when-up-to-date, rebuild-on-change, base-digest storage\n- Server-level tests verifying `EnsureImage` is called during `RunWorkflow` and that failures are properly surfaced\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":272,"cache_read_input_tokens":71970,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":272},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4429857-76e5-431c-977a-09143fc65f99","uuid":"52a48111-4085-4f1c-a86b-888e706bb08b"}
